<h1>News Item Title</h1>

<p>The news item would consist of:</p>
<ul class="content-types">
	<li>Date published</li>
	<li>Categories it was published under</li>
	<li>Full text of the news item</li>
	<li>Images/video inside main text (optional)</li>
</ul>

<div class="helper">
	<h2>Visitor comments</h2>
	<div>
		<p class="rationale">Allow user-generated feedback to help engage with your online audience.</p>
		<p>Listed in order of oldest comment first (so conversations are easy to follow),  each comment consists of:</p>
		<ul class="content-types">
			<li>Author's name</li>
			<li>Date & Time of comment</li>
			<li>Full comment text</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
	<div class="note-block">
		<h3>Notes:</h3>
		<div class="functionality-note">
			<p><strong>FUNCTIONALITY:</strong> The ability to leave comments can be turned off for individual news items if required.</p>
			<p><strong>FUNCTIONALITY:</strong> Comments need to be approved by a site administrator before they appear publicly.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

<div class="helper">
	<h2>Comment form</h2>
	<div>
		<p class="rationale">Capture new comments, fields consist of:</p>
		<ul class="content-types">
			<li>Name</li>
			<li>Email</li>
			<li>Comment text</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
</div>

<div class="helper">
	<h2>List all news categories</h2>
	<div>
		<p class="rationale">List the categories under which News can be posted. This acts as a quick way for people to narrow the list to topics they're interested in.</p>
		<p>Listed alphabetically for easy scanning, each list item would be:</p>
		<ul class="content-types">
			<li>Title of category</li>
			<li>Link to the <a href="/news/category.html">category</a></li>
		</ul>
	</div>
</div>

